BSE - NETHERLANDS (05)
======================
[see
BSE - Netherlands 970323174523
BSE - Netherlands (2) 970324115206
BSE - Netherlands (03) 970406171910
BSE - Netherlands: second case (03) 970407192533]

Date: Fri, 11 Apr 1997 10:55:39 -0400
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Subject: Today's OIE report

11 April 1997
Vol. 10 - No. 15
BOVINE SPONGIFORM ENCEPHALOPATHY IN THE NETHERLANDS
See also: 28 March 1997
Text of a fax received on 8 April 1997 from Dr C.C.J.M. van der Meijs, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Nature Management and
Fisheries, The Hague:
Number of cases confirmed since 1 January 1997: two (2).
Location of the new outbreak: Kollum district (53o 18' N - 6o 10' E),
Friesland province.
Date of detection of the new outbreak: 25 March 1997.
Total number of animals in the new outbreak:
susceptible 70
cases 1
deaths 0
destroyed 70
slaughtered 0
Description of affected population: dairy herd. The animal affected with
bovine spongiform encephalopathy was a 6-year-old cow.
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Institute for Animal Science and
Health of the Department of Agricultural Research (ID-DLO), Lelystad.
B. Diagnostic tests used: histopathological and immunohistochemical research.
Source of agent / origin of infection: tracing on and tracing back for
animals and feedstuffs.
Control measures during reporting period: stamping out.
...........................................mhj
